<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#reproduction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A manifestation/item reproduced in another one.\n\nA reproduction indicates the relationship as it would be drawn from the first manifestation/item in the relationship to the second manifestation/item in the relationship."@en .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#reproduction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has reproduction"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#reproductionOf
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#reproductionOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#reproductionOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#relatedEndeavour> .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#reproductionOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "It identifies the manifestation/item of a reproduced one."@en .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#reproductionOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "is reproduction of"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#responsibleEntity
