<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#supplement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An expression work/expression having another one as supplement.\n\nThe supplement relationship type involves works/expressions that are intended to be used in conjunction with another work/expression. Some of these, such as indices, concordances, teachers' guides, glosses, and instruction manuals for electronic resources will be so closely associated with the content of the related work/expression that they are useless without the other work/expression."@en .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#supplement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has supplement"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#supplementOf
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#supplementOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#supplementOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#relatedEndeavour> .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#supplementOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "It identifies the work/expression of a particular supplement of it."@en .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#supplementOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "is supplement of"@en .
# 
