<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#Item> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A single exemplar of a manifestation.\n\nThe entity defined as item is a concrete entity. It is in many instances a single physical object (e.g., a copy of a one-volume monograph, a single audio cassette, etc.). There are instances, however, where the entity defined as item comprises more than one physical object (e.g., a monograph issued as two separately bound volumes, a recording issued on three separate compact discs, etc.). "@en .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#Item> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "frbr:Item"@en .
